Our kindness and decency towards immigrants like Maira built America. Can we please come together as a nation and not lose that which makes us exceptional. Let’s pass a law that allows Maira to stay and realize her potential in America.

Passing a clean dream act is about believing in the potential and humanity of people like Maira. This is not a Democrat issue or Republican one. This is not about being progressive or conservative. This is about being American.

I grew up in a community that was 95 percent Caucasian in Bucks County, PA. Let me tell you, I don’t know a single person I grew up with in the 1980s who wouldn’t believe that Maira should be able to get a law school education or to be able to pay her respects to her grandfather

She wasn’t able to go see her grandfather’s funeral when he died this past December in Mexico. I know what it’s like to visit grandparents in India. How cruel that she couldn’t even go to mourn her grandparents passing?

She doesn’t qualify for student loans or federal aid. You know I would never have been able to go to law school if I wasn’t allowed to take out hundreds of thousands of loans. Well, Maira doesn’t qualify for any federal loans. Might this incredible talent never get her shot?

She was given legal status after this in DACA. Now our country asks her to fill this form out every two years at a cost of thousands. She has to worry more about this than her education, despite being one of the most eloquent voices of her generation.

She had to spent thousands of legal fees to fill out forms. She had to disclose her medical history, every address where she had lived, and any violation, even tickets, of any law. A single mistake would have put her at risk of being deported.

Please take a few minutes to read Maira Velazquez story and share w/ nation. She is a dreamer who came here from Mexico at four. She is accepted to Santa Clara law school. On our civil rights pilgrimage with @repjohnlewis outside Dr. King’s Dexter church. How are we treating her? https://t.co/7s7mQsznFx
